    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.8"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">T E L E P H O N E
                        <lb/>
                    MADISON SQUARE</hi> 1907-1908
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">SMART SET</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">A Magazine of Cleverness</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">E. F. WARNER, PUBLISHER
                        <lb/>
                    GEORGE JEAN NATHAN
                    AND</hi>                          }<hi rend="italic">Editors</hi>
                    <hi rend="caps">H. L. MENCKEN</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">331 FOURTH AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 15, 1915</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">D.<sic>G.</sic></hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bancroft, Nebr.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>By all means let me see the book. My annual poetry article will be due in a few months. I am sorry indeed that you have no smaller stuff suitable for <title>The Smart Set</title>. If you write any during the coming winter, please do not forget us. Here's hoping that the book will be a big success! Why not send a copy of it to Theodore Dreiser? I think he might be able to do something for it. His address is 165 West 10th Street.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>H.L. Mencken</signed>
                    <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">H. L.</hi> Mencken</note>
                
                    <note>S.A.G.</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
